0that%20fits%20on%20the%20base%20of%20a%20Kettle%20grill%2C%20which%20you%20cover%20with%20the%20lid%3B%20an%20aluminum%20pan%20is%20included.%20The%20Deluxe%20USA%20kit%20includes%20a%20metal%20peel%20and%20pizza%20stone.%20If%20you%20already%20have%20a%20Weber%20Kettle%2C%20this%20is%20by%20far%20the%20best%20value%20you'll%20get%20when%20buying%20a%20pizza%20oven.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20non-Weber%20owners%2C%20KettlePizza%20also%20offers%20pizza%20oven%20kits%20for%20gas%20grills%20that%20sit%20directly%20on%20the%20grill%20grates.%20The%20stainless%20steel%20insert%20reflects%20heat%20down%20to%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20pizza%20and%20can%20reach%20temperatures%20between%20600%20and%20700%20degrees%20F.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20a%20pizza%20oven%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESize%20and%20capacity%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20All%20of%20the%20ovens%20covered%20here%20are%20meant%20to%20cook%20one%20pizza%20at%20a%20time%20very%20quickly.%20A%20model%20with%20a%20wide%20opening%20will%20allow%20you%20the%20space%20necessary%20to%20use%20a%20peel%20to%20maneuver%20your%20pie%20while%20it%20cooks.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20set%20it%20and%20forget%20it%2C%20an%20indoor%20model%20that%20either%20cooks%20your%20pies%20with%20no%20turning%20required%20or%20even%20turns%20them%20for%20you%20might%20be%20a%20better%20fit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaximum%20temperature%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Many%20outdoor%20pizza%20ovens%20can%20reach%20temperatures%20upwards%20of%20900%20degrees.%20While%20cooking%20pizza%20at%20that%20temperature%20is%20common%20in%20restaurants%20and%20pizzerias%2C%20home%20cooks%20might%20want%20to%20shoot%20a%20little%20lower.%20Ken%20Forkish%20prefers%20to%20bake%20pizza%20between%20750%20and%20800%20degrees%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20bake%20a%20pizza%20in%2060%20seconds%20at%20900%20degrees%20you%20need%20to%20be%20really%20good%20because%20you're%20gonna%20have%20to%20turn%20the%20pizza%20a%20few%20times%20in%20that%20period%20and%20you%20also%20need%20to%20have%20particular%20skill%20with%20a%20peel%20%5B...%5D%20These%20kinds%20of%20ovens%20you%20can't%20do%20that.%20There's%20just%20not%20enough%20room%20within%20the%20oven%20to%20treat%20it%20that%20way%20while%20it's%20baking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPortability%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20If%20you%20plan%20on%20bringing%20your%20oven%20to%20parties%20or%20camping%20trips%2C%20choose%20a%20model%20that%20isn't%20too%20heavy%20or%20bulky.%20Many%20brands%20sell%20carrying%20cases%20to%20make%20relocating%20easier.%20If%20you%20anticipate%20storing%20your%20oven%20between%20uses%2C%20it's%20worth%20considering%20size%20and%20weight.%20A%20larger%20oven%20accommodates%20larger%20pies%2C%20but%20will%20also%20take%20longer%20to%20cool%20down%20before%20you%20can%20safely%20store%20it.%20Something%20lighter%20with%20a%20smaller%20footprint%20will%20be%20easier%20to%20set%20up%20and%20tear%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccessories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-pizza-peel%5C%22%3Ebest%20pizza%20peels%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20important%20purchase%20for%20launching%20and%20retrieving%20Neapolitan%20pies.%20Also%2C%20while%20some%20ovens%20ship%20with%20or%20have%20baking%20stones%20built%20into%20them%2C%20we%20recommend%20buying%20any%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-pizza-stone%5C%22%3Ebest%20pizza%20stones%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20your%20model%20doesn't%20have%20one.%20Outdoor%20ovens%20can%20benefit%20from%20a%20cover%20and%2For%20carrying%20case%20for%20inclement%20weather%20and%20pizza-making%20trips%20away%20from%20home.%20Finally%2C%20many%20ovens%20have%20a%20built-in%20thermometer%2C%20but%20an%20infrared%20thermometer%20helps%20to%20manage%20temperature%20fluctuations%20in%20real-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETypes%20of%20pizza%20ovens%