2Fstrong%3E%20Hybrid%20ovens%20offer%20the%20option%20to%20use%20wood%20(or%20wood%20pellets)%2C%20charcoal%2C%20or%20gas%20as%20a%20fuel%20source.%20Some%2C%20like%20the%20Roccbox%2C%20ship%20with%20a%20hose%20to%20connect%20the%20oven%20to%20a%20propane%20tank%20and%20offer%20an%20optional%20attachment%20for%20wood-burning.%20Others%2C%20like%20some%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipgf_080119_best-pizza-ovens-20%26h%3De4330d150dba613d4ee302d60ff987d0f5da26202843583f9ec75d259ea2d050%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f426c2%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fkitchen%252Fbest-pizza-ovens%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fooni.com%252Fpages%252Foven-comparison%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOoni%20pizza%20ovens%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20the%20option%20to%20purchase%20an%20accessory%20to%20attach%20the%20oven%20to%20a%20fixed%20natural%20gas%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EElectric%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Indoor%20ovens%20are%20designed%20to%20sit%20on%20a%20countertop%20and%20plug%20into%20a%20standard%20120%20V%20outlet.%20They're%20great%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20space%20for%20an%20outdoor%20oven%20or%20want%20to%20make%20pizza%20in%20any%20weather.%20The%20electric%20options%20we%20recommend%20have%20lower%20temperature%20ranges%20than%20outdoor%20ovens%2C%20topping%20out%20around%20750%C2%B0%20F.%20However%2C%20with%20heat%20sources%20both%20above%20and%20below%20the%20cook%20surface%20and%20a%20variety%20of%20available%20settings%2C%20you%20can%20still%20make%20fantastic%20pizza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrill%20insert%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECooking%20pizza%20over%20charcoal%20on%20a%20grill%20offers%20a%20similar%20smoky%20flavor%20to%20wood%2C%20but%20can%20require%20tending%20to%20maintain%20consistent%20temperatures%20when%20cooking%20more%20than%20one%20pie.%20It%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20achieve%20the%20high%20temperatures%20necessary%20to%20cook%20Neapolitan-style%20pizza%20quickly%20with%20charcoal%20alone.%20KettleGrill%20recommends%20adding%20hardwood%20chunks%20on%20top%20of%20charcoal%20briquettes%20when%20cooking%20pizza%20if%20you%20want%20to%20achieve%20a%20temperature%20above%20600%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPizza%20oven%20FAQs%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Someone%20pulling%20a%20cooked%20pizza%20out%20of%20a%20Roccbox%20Pizza%20Oven%20with%20a%20pizza%20peel.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646f8b10d6d9d2001856ecbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGozney%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20else%20can%20you%20cook%20in%20a%20pizza%20oven%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPizza%20ovens%20can%20cook%20plenty%20of%20other%20foods%2C%20but%20it%20requires%20some%20strategy.%20Because%20pizza%20ovens%20operate%20at%20extremely%20high%20temperatures%2C%20you%20should%20check%20your%20cookware%20for%20the%20manufacturer's%20recommendations%20for%20maximum%20temperature%20thresholds.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-cast-iron-skillet%5C%22%3Ebest%20cast%20iron%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20good%20bet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKen%20Forkish%20encourages%20home%20cooks%20to%20consider%20the%20dimensions%20of%20their%20oven%20before%20embarking%20on%20non-pizza%20cookery.%20%26quot%3BI%20found%20the%20height%20of%20the%20dome%20in%20these%20small%20portable%20outdoor%20ovens%20is%20very%20much%20relevant%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20With%20a%20lower%20dome%2C%20any%20splatters%20from%20your%20food%20will%20hit%20the%20ceiling%20and%20then%20come%20down%20as%20soot.%20Forkish%20recommends%20the%20Gozney%20Roccbox%20Pizza%20Oven%20for%20cooking%20things%20other%20than%20pizza.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Janjigian%20uses%20his%20Ooni%20oven%20to%20pre-cook%20pizza%20toppings%20and%20sauces%20while%20the%20oven%20is%20heating%20up%20as%20well%20as%20baking%20bread%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20did%20a%20pita%20recipe%20and%20a%20lahmajun%20recipe%2C%20and%20many%20other%20flatbreads%20I%20do%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20clean%20a%20pizza%20oven%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EPizza%20ovens%20are%20meant%20to%20run%20at%20very%20high%20temperatures%2C%20which%20functionally%20is%20like%20running%20your%20residential%20oven%20on%20self-clean%20mode.%20Temperatures%20ranging%20from%20700%20to%20900%20degrees%20F%20and%20above%20get%20rid%20of%20most%20debris%20and%20grime.%20That%20said%2C%20you%20should%20occasionally%20surface%20clean%20the%20inside%20of%20your%20oven%20and%20the%20surface%20of%20your%20stone.%20Be%20sure%20the%20oven%20is%20completely%20cool%20before%20cleaning.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOvens%20with%20chimneys%20may%20periodically%20need%20extra%20soot%20cleaned%20out%20to%20maintain%20optimal%20airflow.%20Avoid%20abrasive%20materials%20and%20harsh%20chemicals%20when%20cleaning%20your%20oven%2C%20opting%20instead%20for%20mild%20soap%20and%20water%2C%20and%20be%20sure%20to%20dry%20all%20surfaces%20thoroughly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20clean%20a%20pizza%20stone%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhow-to-clean-a-pizza-stone%5C%22%3Ecleaning%20a%20pizza%20stone%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20using%20soap.%20Most%20stones%20are%20porous%20and%20can%20absorb%20the%20soapy%20smell%20and%20taste.%20Ooni%2C%20the%20manufacturer%20of%20our%20best%20wood%20fire%20pizza%20oven%2C%20recommends%20removing%20the%20baking%20stone%20from%20their%20oven%2C%20flipping%20it%20over%2C%20and%20placing%20it%20back%20in%20the%20oven%20so%20that%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20stone%20essentially%20cleans%20itself%20in%20the%20high%20heat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5