0have%20had%20more%20methane%20than%20what%20JWST%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20plausible%20answer%20to%20this%20methane%20mystery%20was%20that%20hot%20gas%20from%20deeper%20within%20the%20exoplanet%20was%20vigorously%20mixing%20with%20the%20colder%20gas%20near%20the%20surface%2C%20Welbanks%20and%20Sing%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20these%20new%20measurements%2C%20we're%20actually%20able%20to%20use%20methane%20as%20basically%20a%20thermometer%20into%20the%20interior%2C%20and%20we%20find%20it's%20much%20hotter%20than%20we%20expect%2C%26quot%3B%20Sing%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20teams%20both%20published%20their%20separate%20studies%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22illustration%20of%20james%20webb%20space%20telescope%20with%20gold%20panels%20against%20a%20starry%20purple%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650ab98a961b37edf39af48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22709%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJWST%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20peer%20directly%20into%20a%20planet's%20interior%2C%20but%20it%20can%20gather%20information%20about%20its%20atmosphere%20to%20reveal%20what%20lies%20within.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-james-webb-telescope-13-billion-old-galaxy-not-exist-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJWST's%20observations%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20the%20core%20was%20hotter%20also%20meant%20it%20was%20likely%20much%20larger%2C%20which%20would%20explain%20WASP%20107b's%20big%20diameter.%20Indeed%2C%20both%20Sing%20and%20Welbanks%20concluded%20that%20the%20core%20is%20much%20more%20massive%20than%20the%20original%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Welbanks%20and%20Sing's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdead-planets-broadcast-after-star-explodes-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeasurements%20of%20the%20core%20mass%3C%2Fa%3E%20differ.%20While%20this%20discrepancy%20warrants%20further%20investigation%2C%20both%20studies%20are%20basically%20telling%20the%20same%20story%2C%20said%20Scott%20Gaudi%2C%20professor%20of%20astronomy%20at%20Ohio%20State%20University.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20this%20thing%20is%20puffy%20is%20largely%20due%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpluto-might-be-hiding-a-vast-liquid-ocean-beneath-its-icy-surface-2016-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20internal%20temperature%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gaudi%2C%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20with%20the%20research%20but%20is%20a%20former%20colleague%20with%20a%20co-author%20on%20Welbanks's%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ceeca33-a662-448f-b922-6507c3369aa2%5C%22%3ECollaboration%20is%20key%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20collage%20of%20super%20puffball%20exoplanets%20compared%20to%20planets%20in%20our%20solar%20system%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6661b643d0b8e1c832cc71c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20results%20of%20Sing%20and%20Welbanks'%20collaborative%20research%20could%20inform%20future%20studies%20of%20other%20super%20puffs%2C%20like%20the%20Kepler%2051%20planets.%3Cp%3ENASA%2C%20ESA%2C%20and%20L.%20Hustak%20and%20J.%20Olmsted%20(STScI)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20clarified%20picture%20of%20WASP%20107b's%20interior%20doesn't%20mean%20astronomers%20are%20done%20asking%20questions%20about%20this%20strange%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-super-puff-planets-density-of-cotton-candy-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuper%20puff%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20remaining%20question%20is%20how%20this%20exoplanet's%20core%20got%20to%20be%20so%20hot%2C%20in%20the