%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2Fpvc-pipe-gardening-1-1717506324-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-352048%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESunita%20harvests%20at%20least%205%20kg%20of%20vegetables%20every%20week.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ingenious%20gardeners%20share%20gardening%20tips%20for%20creating%20a%20vertical%20garden%20using%20PVC%20pipes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.Take%20a%20five-foot%20pipe%20and%20cut%20it%20into%20sections%20according%20to%20the%20number%20of%20saplings%20or%20seeds%20you%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Avoid%20drilling%20an%20excessive%20number%20of%20holes%20in%20the%20pipe.%20Maintain%20a%20distance%20of%2018%20inches%20between%20holes%20on%20one%20side%20and%20a%20gap%20of%20nine%20inches%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20of%20the%20pipe.%20In%20total%2C%20there%20should%20be%20five%20evenly%20spaced%20holes%20along%20a%20six-foot%20pipe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Close%20the%20extra%20holes%2C%20if%20any%2C%20using%20a%20hot%20air%20gun.%20Do%20not%20forget%20to%20tape%20the%20extra%20holes%20to%20prevent%20water%20leakage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20Fill%20three-fourth%20part%20of%20the%20pipe%20with%20soil%20and%20plant%20the%20seed%20or%20sapling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20Add%20a%20mixture%20of%20vermicompost%20or%20any%20other%20organic%20fertiliser%20to%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20Create%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20soil%20and%20fill%20it%20with%20sand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20Water%20the%20sand%20so%20that%20it%20stays%20wet%20and%20the%20moisture%20reaches%20the%20bottom%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20There%20is%20no%20need%20to%20change%20the%20soil%20for%20the%20next%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E9.%20New%20saplings%20or%20seeds%20can%20be%20planted%20by%20simply%20making%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E10.%20Neem%20water%20can%20be