20qualities%20in%20me%20shaped%20my%20life%20and%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYears%20later%2C%20when%20he%20got%20married%20and%20became%20a%20father%2C%20he%20found%20that%20he%20could%20not%20support%20his%20family%20as%20doctors%20did%20not%20get%20paid%20well%20in%20India%20at%20the%20time.%20He%20left%20for%20the%20UK%20where%20he%20lived%20for%2012%20years%20and%20completed%20his%20Fellowship%20of%20the%20Royal%20College%20of%20Surgeons%20(FRCS)%20and%20Diploma%20in%20Urology%20in%20the%20UK%20in%201990.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20promised%20my%20mother%20I%20would%20return%20to%20India.%20Also%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20belonging%20to%20India%20though%20I%20was%20well-settled%20in%20the%20UK.%20My%20colleagues%20would%20often%20tease%20me%20about%20the%20kidney%20transplant%20scandals%20in%20India.%20That%20hurt%20my%20feelings%20as%20when%20you%20are%20abroad%2C%20you%20become%20the%20representative%20of%20your%20country.%20I%20wanted%20to%20come%20back%20home%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F270029%2Findia-longest-coma-survivor-dr-jaideep-sharma-organ-donation-register%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edo%20something%20to%20change%20the%20situation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20I%20returned%20in%201995%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201784px)%20100vw%2C%201784px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221784%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Receiving%20his%20PG%20degree%20in%20the%20UK.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391.jpg%201784w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391-300x198.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391-500x331.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391-768x508.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391-1536x1016.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FReceiving-postgraduate-degree-in-urology-and-transplantation-in-the-UK_11zon-1717420391-150x99.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351937%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221180%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EReceiving%20his%20PG%20degree%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBoost%20for%20deceased%20organ%20donation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20opportune%20time%20to%20return.%20The%20government%20then%20had%20just%20passed%20the%20Transplantation%20of%20Human%20Organs%20%26amp%3B%20Tissues%20Act%20(THOTA)%2C%201994.%20The%20law%20accepted%20brain%20death%20as%20legal%20death%20which%20was%20a%20huge%20boost%20for%20deceased%20organ%20donation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F311982%2Fmumbai-hansa-raghwani-fought-stage-four-cancer-chemotherapy-surgery-recovery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfter%20a%20natural%20cardiac%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20a%20few%20organs%20and%20tissues%20can%20be%20donated%20(like%20the%20cornea%2C%20bones%2C%20skin%20and%20blood%20vessels)%2C%20but%20after%20a%20brain%20death%2C%20eight%20solid%20organs%2C%20including%20the%20vital%20organs%20like%20kidneys%2C%C2%A0heart%2C%C2%A0liver%C2%A0and%C2%A0lungs%2C%20and%20almost%2050%20tissues%2C%20can%20be%20donated%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Act%20also%20made%20commercial%20dealings%20in%20human%20organs%20a%20punishable%20offence.%20It%20is%20the%20toughest%20law%20in%20the%20world%20as%20far%20as%20organ%20donation%20is%20concerned.%20The%20number%20of%20scams%20in%20kidneys%20have%20come%20down%20considerably%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Shroff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20renal%20transplant%20surgeon%2C%20he%20became%20aware%20of%20the%20huge%20shortage%20of%20kidneys%20in%20India.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20see%20the%20agony%20and%20desperation%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20caregivers%20and%20family%20members%20when%20no%20suitable%20kidney%20donor%20was%20available%20in%20the%20family.%20So%2C%20we%20had%20to%20have%20an%20alternative%20to%20%E2%80%98live%20donations%E2%80%99.%20The%20answer%20was%20deceased%20organ%20donation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20was%20no%20support%20system%20or%20awareness%20in%20the%20country%20at%20that%20time.%20The%20doctors%20themselves%20felt%20that%20brain%20death%20was%20too%20complex%20to%20be%20accepted%20by%20the%20public.%20They%20did%20not%20feel%20that%20deceased%20organ%20transplantation%20was%20possible%20in%20India%2C%20he%20rues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201500px)%20100vw%2C%201500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FSpeaking-at-a-conference_11zon-1717421181.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Shroff%20speaking%20at%20a%20conference.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FSpeaking-at-a-conference_11zon-1717421181.jpg%201500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FSpeaking-at-a-conference_11zon-1717421181-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FSpeaking-at-a-conference_11zon-1717421181-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FSpeaking-at-a-conference_11zon-1717421181-768x512.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FSpeaking-at-a-conference_11zon-1717421181-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351958%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Shroff%20speaking%20at%20a%20conference.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEstablishing%20MOHAN%20Foundation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20why%20we%20set%20up%20the%20not-for-profit%20MOHAN%20Foundation.%20It%20was%20meant%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F206018%2Fhow-to-donate-organs-body-in-india-process-rules-donation-eligibility%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20raise%20awareness%20about%20brain%20death%20and%20deceased%20organ%20donation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20we%20soon%20realised%20that%20was%20not%20enough%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Shroff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20needed%20to%20train%20ICU%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20in%20identifying%20brain%20death%2C%20organ%20retrieval%2C%20counselling%20and%20support%20families%20at%20the%20time%20of%20their%20grief.%20Along%20with%20this%2C%20we%20also%20had%20to%20put%20systems%20in%20place%20at%20hospitals%2C%20and%20sensitise%20not%20only%20the%20general%20public%20but%20also%20the%20medical%20fraternity%20on%20this%20topic%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MOHAN%20Foundation%20focuses%20on%20deceased%20organ%20donation%20for%20two%20reasons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20heart%2C%20lungs%2C%20pancreas%20and%20intestines%2C%20the%20organs%20have%20to%20come%20from%20a%20deceased%20person.%20Live%20donations%20can%20only%20take%20place%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20kidney%20and%20part%20of%20the%20liver.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%2C%20deceased%20organ%20donation%20and%20transplantation%20is%20a%20complex%20process%20that%20needs%20coordination%20between%20multiple%20stakeholders%2C%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20used%20technology%20extensively.%20We%20have%20software%20that%20finds%20out%20which%20patient%20on%20the%20waiting%20list%20should%20be%20given%20the%20next%20available%20organ.%20We%20use%20apps%20to%20identify%20and%20certify%20brain%20death.%20We%20also%20use%20AI%20to%20predict%20organ%20failure%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Shroff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20foundation%20has%20counselled%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20families%20successfully%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F208322%2Fbengaluru-teen-teacher-death-blood-donation-community-inspiring-india-say143%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20donate%20the%20organs%20of%20their%20loved%20ones%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewho%20are%20declared%20brain-dead.%20The%20conversion%20rate%20of%20such%20cases%20is%20high%20at%2060-70%25.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organisation%20has%20sensitised%20over%20250%20million%20people%20on%20organ%20donation%20and%20trained%20around%204%2C000%20grief%20counsellors%20or%20transplant%20coordinators%20and%20more%20than%2061%2C000%20medical%20professionals%20on%20organ%20donation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20foundation%20has%20issued%20over%202.5%20million%20donor%20cards.%20It%20has%20a%20helpline%20number%3A%2018001037100%20where%20queries%20on%20kidney%2C%20liver%20and%20other%20transplants%20are%20answered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMOHAN%20Foundation%20has%20offices%20in%20Chennai%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Imphal%2C%20Delhi-NCR%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20Nagpur%2C%20Jaipur%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20and%20the%20USA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20inked%20MoUs%20with%20nine%20state%20governments%2C%20including%20Uttarakhand%20and%20Manipur.%20In%202011%2C%20when%20the%20law%20was%20being%20amended%2C%20the%20foundation%20came%20up%20with%20several%20recommendations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20authorities%20ensure%20that%20hospitals%20have%20transplant%20coordinators%20before%20giving%20licences.%20Since%20April%202018%2C%20when%20a%20person%20applies%20for%20a%20driving%20licence%2C%20there%20is%20a%20pop-up%20from%20the%20transport%20authority%20asking%20whether%20he%20or%20she%20would%20like%20to%20pledge%20organs.%20The%20ICU%20doctors%20are%20also%20morally%20obligated%20to%20ask%20for%20organs%20from%20the%20family%20in%20case%20of%20a%20brain%20death.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201500px)%20100vw%2C%201500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FThe-MOHAN-Foundation-team_11zon-1717421127.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20MOHAN%20Foundation%20team.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FThe-MOHAN-Foundation-team_11zon-1717421127.jpg%201500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FThe-MOHAN-Foundation-team_11zon-1717421127-300x199.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FThe-MOHAN-Foundation-team_11zon-1717421127-500x332.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FThe-MOHAN-Foundation-team_11zon-1717421127-768x510.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FThe-MOHAN-Foundation-team_11zon-1717421127-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351954%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20MOHAN%20Foundation%20team.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESignificant%20rise%20in%20numbers%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Global%20Observatory%20on%20Donation%20and%20Transplantation%2C%20India%20has%20witnessed%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20deceased%20organ%20donations%20post%20COVID-19.%20It%20surpassed%20a%20milestone%20by%20transitioning%20from%20three-digit%20donations%20to%20four%20digits%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20having%20had%20a%20total%20of%201%2C037%20deceased%20donors%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20India%20conducted%20a%20total%20of%2012%2C526%20kidney%20transplants%2C%2010%2C896%20from%20living%20donors%20and%201%2C630%20from%20deceased%20donors.%20Additionally%2C%20there%20were%204%2C173%20liver%20transplants%2C%20including%203%2C338%20from%20living%20donors%20and%20828%20from%20deceased%20donors.%20There%20were%20221%20total%20heart%20transplants%2C%20191%20liver%2C%2021%20pancreas%20and%2014%20small%20bowel%20transplants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChallenges%20faced%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Directorate%20General%20of%20Health%20Services%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Family%20Welfare%2C%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20some%20of%20the%20challenges%20in%20deceased%20organ%20donation%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHuge%20demand-supply%20gap.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPoor%20infrastructure%2C%20especially%20in%20government%20hospitals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20awareness%20of%20brain%20death%20among%20stakeholders.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPoor%20rate%20of%20brain%20death%20certification%20by%20hospitals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20awareness%20and%20negative%20attitude%20towards%20deceased%20organ%20donation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20organised%20systems%20for%20organ%20procurement%20from%20deceased%20donors.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaintenance%20of%20standards%20in%20organ%20retrieval%2C%20tissue%20banking%2C%20and%20transplantation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHigh%20cost%20of%20transplantation%2C%20especially%20for%20uninsured%20and%20poor%20patients.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20DGHS%2C%20the%20National%20Organ%20and%20Tissue%20Transplant%20Organisation%20(NOTTO)%20takes%20responsibility%20for%20the%20following%20actions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaintaining%20the%20waiting%20list%20of%20terminally%20ill%20patients%20requiring%20transplants%20%E2%80%93%20with%20details%20of%20hospital%2C%20organ%20needed%2C%20blood%20group%20and%20age%20of%20patient%2C%20urgency%2C%20and%20seniority%20in%20the%20waiting%20list.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMatching%20recipients%20with%20donors.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENetworking%20with%20transplant%20centres%2C%20retrieval%20centres%20and%20tissue%20banks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECoordination%20of%20all%20activities%20required%20for%20procurement%20of%20organs%20and%20tissues%2C%20including%20medico-legal%20aspects.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAssigning%20the%20organ%20retrieval%20team%20and%20making%20arrangements%20for%20transporting%20the%20organs%20to%20the%20allocated%20locations.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20796px)%20100vw%2C%20796px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22796%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Actress%20Revathi%20holding%20up%20her%20donor%20card.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930.jpg%20796w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-768x511.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351951%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EActress%20Revathi%20holding%20up%20her%20donor%20card.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECounselling%20the%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Dr%20Shroff%20set%20up%20a%20protocol%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Ramachandra%20Protocol%E2%80%99%20while%20asking%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20consent%20for%20organ%20donation.%20The%20doctors%20would%20start%20by%20asking%20for%20eye%20donation%20first%20since%20it%20was%20already%20popular%2C%20and%20then%20for%20the%20other%20organs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTalking%20about%20organ%20donation%20is%20not%20easy%20at%20a%20time%20of%20grief.%20We%20need%20to%20treat%20the%20grieving%20family%20sensitively%20and%20support%20them.%20We%20have%20to%20first%20convey%20to%20the%20family%20that%20their%20loved%20one%20is%20brain%20dead.%20We%20need%20to%20then%20explain%20what%20brain%20death%20is.%20We%20let%20the%20message%20sink%20in%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20five%20to%20six%20hours%2C%20before%20we%20switch%20off%20the%20ventilator%2C%20we%20ask%20the%20family%20whether%20they%20wish%20to%20donate%20the%20organs.%20We%20tell%20them%20that%20they%20can%20save%20many%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20brain%20deaths%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F131027%2Fblood-donation-record-rotary%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edue%20to%20road%20accidents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Doctors%20have%20two%20to%20three%20days%20after%20brain%20deaths%20to%20do%20a%20transplant%20surgery.%20Certifying%20a%20brain%20death%20is%20a%20complex%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20the%20counsellors%20start%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20family.%20If%20the%20family%20is%20convinced%2C%20multiple%20organs%20are%20harvested%20and%20distributed%20for%20transplant%20as%20per%20the%20waiting%20list%20of%20recipients.%20There%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20team%20work%20involved%20which%20is%20done%20by%20coordinators%20trained%20by%20the%20MOHAN%20Foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAge%20is%20no%20bar%20for%20organ%20donation.%20Our%20oldest%20donor%20was%20an%2088-year-old%20trustee%20of%20the%20Gangaram%20Hospital.%20When%20he%20was%20declared%20brain%20dead%2C%20his%20kidneys%20and%20liver%20were%20transplanted.%20However%2C%20we%20are%20cautious%20about%20taking%20the%20heart%20and%20lungs%20of%20a%20donor%20who%20is%20above%2060%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Shroff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201768px)%20100vw%2C%201768px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWith-a-donor-family-in-Seattle-US_11zon-1717420865.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22At%20a%20function%20to%20felicitate%20organ%20donor%20families%20in%20Seattle.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWith-a-donor-family-in-Seattle-US_11zon-1717420865.jpg%201768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWith-a-donor-family-in-Seattle-US_11zon-1717420865-300x196.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWith-a-donor-family-in-Seattle-US_11zon-1717420865-500x327.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWith-a-donor-family-in-Seattle-US_11zon-1717420865-768x502.jpg%20768w%2C%